{"TopicId":191880,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"v1.9 Cannot adjust 2nd maneuver node on map ?","CreatedByName":"boolybooly","CreatedById":6572,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-23T19:05:35Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"boolybooly","CreatedById":6572,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-23T19:05:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAm I the only one? Or is this a new \u0022feature\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen adding secondary\u002B\u002B maneuver nodes to a flight plan I cannot adjust them using the widget in the map, I can set them up in a location as usual using RMB but can only change them using the interface Maneuver Mode panel, usually lower left corner, either numerically or using the panel\u00A0widget.\u00A0 It used to be the case that you could adjust them in the map, which is what I am used to doing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tested this in sandpit mode and tried various settings for conic patch draw mode\u00A0and limit\u00A0because these were the only things I could see which might have an effect but they did not change this. Can anyone advise what is going on here?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWin7 instal via steam, unmodded.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-23T19:06:49Z\u0022 title=\u002202/23/2020 07:06  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 23, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by boolybooly\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-23T19:07:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re not alone, it\u0027s a confirmed bug\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/24840\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/24840\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"boolybooly","CreatedById":6572,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-23T19:14:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/196199-voidsquid/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022196199\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/196199-voidsquid/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@VoidSquid\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0, that explains it ! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-23T19:22:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re welcome\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom what I did read in the last couple of days, 1.9. has a not so small number of issues, from \u003Ca href=\u0022https://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/24871\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eexploding Kerbals\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E,\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/191632-game-crashes-on-startup-with-unity-window/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#3d6594;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EUnity crashes when trying to start KSP\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0which did not happen in earlier versions (not completely true, I remember an issue people had with AMD cards), and the\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://bugs.kerbalspaceprogram.com/issues/24848\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#3d6594;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EMun becoming an ice skating arena\u003C/a\u003E, plus of course the \u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003Emaneuver node editing issue you mentioned,\u00A0\u003C/span\u003EI\u0027d think about staying with 1.8.1 and update/upgrade when at least the severe issues will be fixed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-23T19:27:08Z\u0022 title=\u002202/23/2020 07:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 23, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by VoidSquid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-24T13:25:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis was entered into the bug tracker nearly two weeks ago. It\u0027s not a minor bug; it makes missions beyond the Mun pretty much unplayable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002266485\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/66485-squad/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SQUAD\u003C/a\u003E, I\u0027m sure I\u0027m not the only one who\u0027s disappointed no action (the bug tracker status is pegged at \u002210%\u0022) seems to be taken to fix this. What\u0027s the point of updating Moho textures if you can\u0027t get there?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-24T13:36:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/78303-kerbart/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002278303\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/78303-kerbart/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Kerbart\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Well, it\u0027s not the first time we\u0027re seeing this, and so far, the 1.x.y all sorted out the issues, y= 1...5.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESome patience, and it\u0027s not that 1.8.1 is working not fine \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-24T16:21:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223746466\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191880\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221582551380\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022VoidSquid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, VoidSquid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/78303-kerbart/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002278303\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/78303-kerbart/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Kerbart\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Well, it\u0027s not the first time we\u0027re seeing this, and so far, the 1.x.y all sorted out the issues, y= 1...5.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know... up until now the bugs I\u0027ve encountered were of the \u0022\u003Cem\u003EWhen I do x, y happens... Well, don\u0027t do x then!\u003C/em\u003E\u0022 type but I have no mitigation for this one and it frustrates me a little bit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith various space stations in orbit that have the release valve my save doesn\u0027t work in 1.8.1 - but I\u0027ll manage.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-25T09:20:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223746535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191880\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221582561286\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278303\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbart\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, Kerbart said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nrelease valve my save doesn\u0027t work in 1.8.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBummer...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m using this mod since ages to get rid of fuel I don\u0027t need anymore:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8816271869\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/186526-18x-tac-fuel-balancer/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:231px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut that wouldn\u0027t help you with your vessels that already have that new valve.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}